Actress Tonto Dikeh has gone the extra mile to get her young son, King Andre an extraordinary birthday gift. The film star welcomed her son with ex-husband Churchill Olakunle six years ago and on each birthday has made it a point of call to gift him something different and bigger. For his 6th birthday, King Andre was gifted a piece of Scotland’s real estate by his loving mother. Dikeh took to her Instagram page on Thursday to share beautiful photos and videos of her son’s birthday.   Mr Ibu’s daughter sets to wed US-based lover     I’m glad I cohabited with my wife before marriage…     Funke Akindele’s ‘Omo Ghetto The Saga’ becomes most watched…   - Advertisement - She revealed his birthday present alongside the deeds of his land. She also appreciated the legendary American rapper, Snoop Dogg and her friend, Ogechukwu for aiding in the acquisition of her son’s ‘extra’ gift. Sharing a photo of the deed, Tontolet wrote: “Planning your future has been the most important event for me. “FOR THIS YEAR I GO MY BABY @kingandre_dikeh a piece of SCOTTLAND’s REAL ESTATE and his Deeds came with a TITLE AS ‘LORD’ and a Tree planted in his honor and Name. “I am so proud of how far we have come as a team.” “A big thanks to My girl @glogeworld and my uncle @snoopdogg for helping me get this lifetime real estate investment.” SPONSORED